{
  "text": "The stria terminalis is a bundle of fibers in the brain that serves as a major pathway carrying messages to and from the amygdala. Studies have shown a possible relation between the stria terminalis and addiction processes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Emerging evidence suggests that the stria terminalis may play a significant role in anxiety [CITATION_3] . Therefore, future work is needed to investigate emotional changes and their connection to brain alterations in SPD subjects.",
